The paper deals with a network communication problem involving relays and resource allocation to optimize throughput. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of relays and optimization of resource allocation also suggests the possibility of research in signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper also addresses the optimization of transmission protocols, which is a topic in systems and control (cs.SY).
